<h2 class="bac"><img class="pclose" src="../images/clear.gif">Our Business</h2>
<div>
<h3 class="bac">Summary</h3>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Locations London and various other European and Emerging Markets (ex-Asia) locations</li>
	<li>Desk-specific, varying in length from 3 - 6 months</li>
	<li>Strong A-level grades and on track for a minimum 2:1 degree (or equivalent)</li>
	<li>Fluency in English and a second European language may also be required for some roles</li>
</ul>
<p class="bac">Global Capital Markets originates a wide variety of equity and debt capital offerings, as well as risk management products. When an issuer client decides to raise capital in the public or private markets, corporate and investment bankers turn to the Global Capital Markets team. Global Capital Markets partners the coverage team and advises clients on optimal methods to access capital, whether for acquisitions, refinancing or strengthening their balance sheets. The offerings can comprise equities, bonds, bank debt, private placements or a combination of securities.</p>
<p class="bac">The Debt Capital Markets team raises capital for the firm&#39;s clients through the origination, development and execution of instruments across the debt spectrum. Equity Capital Markets originates, structures, and executes worldwide equity and equity-linked products on behalf of the firm&#39;s global corporate client base.</p>
</div></div>

<div class="expand">
<h2 class="bac"><img class="popen" src="../images/clear.gif">Overview</h2>
<div>
<p class="bac nobr">As an intern within Global Capital Markets, you&#39;ll:</p>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Work as a product specialist to create and deliver financing solutions through debt, equity, equity-linked and derivative products to the company&#39;s clients</li>
	<li>Provide market-informed judgments on a broad array of financing strategies to address clients&#39; specific needs</li>
	<li>Work on live transactions and interact with clients as you build your network and experience</li>
	<li>Help generate ideas and opportunities for new and existing clients through in-depth research, financial modeling and industry analyses</li>
</ul>
</div></div>

<div class="expand">
<h2 class="bac"><img class="popen" src="../images/clear.gif">Training</h2>
<div>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>On-the-desk training specific to your desk allocation</li>
	<li>A buddy and mentoring programme</li>
	<li>Constructive feedback sessions through performance evaluations</li>
	<li>Opportunities to interact with senior bankers and network with peers</li>
</ul>
</div></div>

<div class="expand">
<h2 class="bac"><img class="popen" src="../images/clear.gif">Qualifications</h2>
<div>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Applications are accepted from a diverse range of degree disciplines such as the arts and humanities, as well as numerically focused subjects such as economics and mathematics</li>
	<li>Strong A-level grades and on track for a minimum 2:1 degree (or equivalent)</li>
	<li>Fluency in English is essential and a second European language may also be required for some roles</li>
	<li>You&#39;ll need to demonstrate drive, innovation and a genuine interest in the financial markets</li>
	<li>Team-working, leadership and problem-solving skills, plus creativity are key qualities, as is the ability to work in a fast-paced environment, multi-task and interact with a variety of people</li>
</ul>
</div></div>

